Sentencas: Relationships are derived by means of which data on the ionic and electronic conductivity of the electrolyte employed in a fuel cell can be calculated from the U-I curves of the cell, provided that certain conditions in regard to the extent of electrode polarization are met.
Titulo: Information content of the voltage vs. current curve of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The capability and limitations of the resulting equations are demonstrated on the basis of known data on the ionic conductivity of gadolinia doped ceria.
Titulo: Information content of the voltage vs. current curve of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: By applying the relationships to recently published performance data of fuel cells with CuFeO2 as electrolyte or as part of a composite electrolyte, the partial conductivities of this oxide are quantified for the first time.
Titulo: Information content of the voltage vs. current curve of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results prove that CuFeO2, known to be a good mixed ionic-electronic conductor, exhibits unexpectedly high oxygen-ion conductivity under the operating conditions of a fuel cell.
Titulo: Information content of the voltage vs. current curve of a solid oxide fuel cell
